<div id="review_4068680046" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4068680046" />
    <a title="nia" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/94035714-nia"><img alt="nia" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1610002358p2/94035714.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4068680046?book_show_action=true">Jun 21, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="nia" class="user" itemprop="url" name="nia" href="/user/show/94035714-nia">nia</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4068680046" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4508790063945590447">this is just a superb book--moving, clear-eyed, sharp, and complicated. trigger warning for sexual assault and racism, of course, as those are attendant evils to this story. i am so fascinated by condé&apos;s tituba and what a full, three-dimensional character she is. and i was so struck by the underlying message of love and a constant refusal to give in to the bitterness and hatred of those surrounding her. tituba&apos;s rejection of hatred and violence and embrace of generative love and healing is alway</span>
  <span id="freeText4508790063945590447" style="display:none">this is just a superb book--moving, clear-eyed, sharp, and complicated. trigger warning for sexual assault and racism, of course, as those are attendant evils to this story. i am so fascinated by condé's tituba and what a full, three-dimensional character she is. and i was so struck by the underlying message of love and a constant refusal to give in to the bitterness and hatred of those surrounding her. tituba's rejection of hatred and violence and embrace of generative love and healing is always a deliberate, carefully calculated choice, made not because it is simple or easy, but rather because it is right. that's something that i find so difficult in my own life, and it's incredible that condé pinned it to the page with deceptive ease.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4508790063945590447" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


