        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2565219023" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13651245128930277331">This book is an imagined history of an actual person, Tituba. A person I didn&apos;t know existed until this year. Tituba was a black woman persecuted during the Salem witch trials in 17th century Puritan America.<br/><br/>Tituba&apos;s herstory comes to life in this imagining - complete with parody and current day intersections of feminism and racism.<br/><br/>This edition also had an author interview from the early 1990s that reveals a lot of information about the French novelist and the genre of Caribbean literature that </span>
  <span id="freeText13651245128930277331" style="display:none">This book is an imagined history of an actual person, Tituba. A person I didn't know existed until this year. Tituba was a black woman persecuted during the Salem witch trials in 17th century Puritan America.<br /><br />Tituba's herstory comes to life in this imagining - complete with parody and current day intersections of feminism and racism.<br /><br />This edition also had an author interview from the early 1990s that reveals a lot of information about the French novelist and the genre of Caribbean literature that I also found fascinating.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13651245128930277331" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


